      The Dashboard helps you explore, create, and share data visualizations about the Internet.
    </div>
  </div>

  <div class="block-link">
    <div class="block-link-icon">
      <div class="block-link-icon-bg"></div>
    </div>
    <div class="block-link-body">
      <h4 class="block-link-header">AccessCheck</h4>
      AccessCheck lets users test websites in different countries to see whether they're available. 
    </div>
  </div>

  <div class="block-link">
    <div class="block-link-icon">
      <div class="block-link-icon-bg"></div>
    </div>
    <div class="block-link-body">
      <h4 class="block-link-header">Country Views</h4>
      Country Views provide collections of currated data and widgets relevant to each country.
    </div>
  </div>

  <div class="block-link">
    <div class="block-link-icon">
      <div class="block-link-icon-bg"></div>
    </div>
    <div class="block-link-body">
      <h4 class="block-link-header">Research</h4>
      Research publications high-lighting some of the more fascinating developments and debates in the networked world.
    </div>
  </div>

  <div class="block-link">
    <div class="block-link-icon">
      <div class="block-link-icon-bg"></div>
    </div>
    <div class="block-link-body">
      <h4 class="block-link-header">Data</h4>
      Documentation of all of Internet Monitor's data streams, filtering data offerings, and APIs
    </div>
  </div>

  <div class="block-link">
    <div class="block-link-icon">
      <div class="block-link-icon-bg"></div>
    </div>
    <div class="block-link-body">
      <h4 class="block-link-header">About</h4>
      More information on Internet Monitor's efforts, organization, and offerings.
    </div>
  </div>
</div>

<div class="container">
  <div class="blog-posts">
    <h2> Recent Blog Posts </h2>
    <% recent_posts.each do |p| %>
      <%= render "/refinery/blog/posts/recent_post", post: p %>
    <% end %>
    <%= link_to "See all blog posts Â»", blog_root_path %>
  </div>

  <% cache( 'thenetmonitor-tweets', expires_in: 5.minutes ) { %>
    <section class="twitter">
      <!--<%= DateTime.now %>-->
      <h1>Latest Tweets from @thenetmonitor</h1>
      <ul class="tweets">
        <% imon_tweets.each do |tweet| %>
          <li><%= raw auto_link( tweet.text ) %></li>
        <% end %>
      </ul>
      <div class="follow"><span>Follow</span> <a href="https://twitter.com/thenetmonitor">@thenetmonitor</a><br><span>on Twitter</span></div>
    </section>
  <% } %>
</div>
